snippet: The Russian-American deal to destroy Syria’s chemical weapons gives President Obama some breathing space, but the list of things that could still go wrong is daunting.
abstract: Russian-American deal to destroy Syria’s chemical weapons arsenal gives Pres Obama some breathing space after a politically damaging few weeks, but negotiating deadlock, Syrian interference and number of other factors could still cause plan to go awry; Obama has decided to leave warships in eastern Mediterranean to preserve possibility of military strike, but administration has yet to formulate specific alternative if agreement fails.
lead_paragraph: The Russian-American deal to destroy Syria’s chemical weapons gives President Obama some breathing space, but the list of things that could still go wrong is daunting.

headline.main: Brief Respite for President, but No Plan B on Syria
